txt.en: 'While I was able to escape the camp and come here to seek aid, many of my fellows were not so fortunate. I would ask you to free them. Their imprisonment is unjust, but I also fear they would become hostages when Torthril marches on Pahor Boha.'
'Thank you for rescuing them. Had any of the other warriors helped them, they would have suffered repercussions.'
'I will make for Ost Arnd√≠r at once!'
The warrior merely inclines his head at you before fleeing
Upokhir has asked you to rescue some fellow dissenters in Pahor Boha.\n\nPahor Boha can be found in the south-east of Pinnath Gelin.
Many dissenters have been imprisoned at Pahor Boha. Upokhir would have you rescue them.
You to have rescued the imprisoned warriors within Pahor Boha and should report your success.\n\nTalk to Upokhir in Ost Arndir.
